Chapter 2 - Basic HTML tags

We can add elements inside the body to define the page layout.

HTML Element
Everything from starting to the ending tag

<body> opening tag
 content
</body> closing tag

HTML attributes
Used to add more information corresponding to an HTML tag
Example : <a href="https://xyz.com/"> XYZ </a>

here,
a= anchor tag
href= attribute

We can either use single or double quotes in attribures

We can either use single or double quotes in attributes

The Heading tag
Heading tag is used to mark heading in HTML from h1 to h5, we have tags for the most important to the least important heading

<h1>Most important heading</h1>
<h2>Another Important heading</h2>
<h3>Another Important heading</h3>
<h4>Another Important heading</h4>
<h5>Another Important heading</h5>
<h6>Another Important heading</h6>

NOTE: we should not use HTML heading to make text thick and bold

The Paragraph Tag
Paragraph are used to add pragraphs to an HTML page
<p> The is para</p>

The Anchor Tag
The Anchor tag is used to add links to an existing content inside an HTML page
<a href="https://google.com"> GUGURU </a>

The img Tag
img tag is used to add images in an HTML page
<img src="image.jpg">

Bold, italic and uderline tags
We can use bold, italic and uderline tags to highlight the text as follows
<b>BOLD</b>
<i>Itlic</i>
<u>Uderline</u>

break tag ie br 
the br tag is used to create line breaks in an HTML documents

Big and small tags
We can make the text a bit larger and bit smaller using big and small tags respectively

hr tag
<hr> tag in HTML is used to create a horizontal ruler ofter used to seperate the context

Subscript and superscript
We can add subscript and superscripts in HTML as follows:
<sub>this</sub> is subscript
<sup> this </sup> is super script


pre tag
HTML always ignores extra spaces and newlines. In order to disply a piece of text as is, we use pre tag
<pre>
    This is written
    using pre
    tag
</pre>

I will rendered as is

